    229          //---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    230          /**
    231           * @brief      Starts the validation of the specified block from the specified table
    232           * @details     The block_address should be start address of the Block defined in the FIT table
    233           *
    234           * @param table - table to be validated should be from the FITMGR_TABLE_TYPE list
    235           * @param block_address - Start address of the block to be validated
    236          
    237           * @return
    238           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_IDLE          -   This is returned by FITMgr__GetStatus() if the handler is in IDLE state
    239           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_BUSY          -   If the Handler is busy in processing the previous requests,
    240           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_ACCEPTED      -   Request is accepted and started processing
    241           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_VALID         -   This is returned by FITMgr__GetStatus() if the integrity is valid for the requested table
    242           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_INVALID       -   This is returned by FITMgr__GetStatus() if the integrity is invalid for the requested table
    243           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_INVALID_TABLE -   If the requested is not registered in the FITMGR_TABLE_TYPE or the Table format is corrupted
    244           *      @retval FITMGR_STATUS_INVALID_BLOCK -   If the table contains 0 blocks except the Header and Footer or
